Rule: Higher education (Prof-school, Doctorate, Bachelors) leads to higher income.
Occupation in the Service industry leads to higher income, even if the workclass remains the same.
Workclass being "Other/Unknown" can still lead to higher income if paired with higher education.
Reduced hours per week (from 40 to 10) can lead to higher income if education level is increased (Bachelors in this case).
